post_text:
Message from our Superintendent of Schools:

Greetings, this is Dr. Anthony Martinez, Superintendent of Schools of the Montebello Unified School District, reminding you that our first day of school is this Monday, August 19th. We are enthusiastic with your return and hope for a successful school year. The education provided will be focused on our new vision statement: Empowering Students to Achieve Academic Excellence as Model Citizens.
Thank you

Mensaje de nuestro Superintendente de Escuelas:

¡Hola! soy el Dr. Anthony Martínez, Superintendente de Escuelas del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Montebello, recordándoles que el primer día de clases es este lunes 19 de agosto. Estamos entusiasmados con su regreso y esperamos tener un año escolar exitoso. La educación proporcionada tendrá como enfoque nuestra nueva visión: Empoderando a los estudiantes para que alcancen la excelencia académica como ciudadanos modelo.
Gracias

Montebello Unified School District in association with the Latino Film Institute Youth Cinema Project is proud to present our Second Annual Film Festival!

Please join us in attending this Red Carpet Event featuring a series of short films directed and produced by our film students at Greenwood Elementary, Bell Gardens Intermediate, Eastmont Intermediate, Suva Intermediate, Bell Gardens High School, and Schurr High School. Taking place Wednesday, June 5, 2019 from 4:00 p.m. to 8:00 p.m. at the Bell Gardens High School Auditorium.

Come enjoy an evening of friends, family & film!

Thank you for supporting the Arts!

post_text:
Visit and presentations from Universidad de Guadalajara on Dia de Los Muertos

Oct. 9 through Oct. 12 students from both La Merced Elementary and La Merced Intermediate had the opportunity to learn about and participate in Dia de los Muertos (Day of the Dead) activities. Students started by receiving a culturally enriching history lesson where they learned the origins, traditions, and practices of Dia de Los Muertos. The week then culminated with the students getting to work on their own altars and displaying them for their fellow students to experience and see. Thank you to our visitors and guest from La Universidad de Guadalajara for such a wonderful experience.

post_text:
Congratulations to all our new ASB/ Student Body Presidents! Miguel Sanchez-Tortoledo from Bell Gardens High School, Sharlize Pettite from Montebello High School, Johnathan Martinez from Schurr High School, Brenda Cobos Molina from Vail High School, Sebastian Camacho from the Applied Technology Center, and a special welcome and congratulations to Melvin Chicas from Montebello Community Day School who will now also join the rest of the student body representatives in presenting updates at our Board of Education meetings! Our student body representatives had the opportunity to tour our District Office earlier in the day and then came back to present at our Board of Education meeting last week on September 6, 2018. We wish them the best of luck and a great year!

In addition to our student body representatives, our Board of Education also recognized our Community Day School team on receiving a WASC accreditation!

post_text: Over 450 Young Latina students from throughout the Montebello Unified School District had the chance to participate in the 23rd Annual Adelante Mujer Latina Conference at Pasadena City College on Saturday April 22nd! Our young girls had a full day of listening to motivational speakers and attending several workshops hosted by experts and leaders in a variety of industries and career fields. The ultimate goal of the conference was to provide our students with the tools that will help them with personal and professional growth and encourage them to pursue and continue their education after high school.

post_text: Congratulations to Jonathan Nguyen from Macy Intermediate who is first place winner of the MUSD district-wide Spelling Bee! The Spelling Bee took place last Wednesday, February 15, 2017 at Schurr High School. Forty-four students from throughout the district were present and competed. In the end, after 18 rounds, Jonathan Nguyen spelled the word "extraordinary" winning him first place in the competition. Jonathon will now go on to compete and represent MUSD at the Los Angeles County Spelling Bee. The Los Angeles County Spelling Bee will take place March 29, 2017. Jonathan will compete with students from throughout Los County and if he places in the top two he will then go on to compete in the California State Spelling Bee. Congratulations and Good Luck!!

post_text:
Congratulations to Suva Elementary on a successful AVID Showcase!

SUE was chosen by the AVID Center to host the showcase that received great recognition throughout the region for their implementation of AVID strategies leading to student success! This showcase was a great opportunity to see AVID at SUE, known also as Suva University in Action! During the showcase districts had the opportunity to learn how to implement the AVID College Readiness System, meet with key site leadership to hear highlights of AVID’s districtwide affect, and hear directly from teachers, students and parents about the impact of AVID Elementary.

Once again Congratulations to SUE and the entire team for their great work! Please visit AVID.org to learn more about the program.
